-- UCLA’s Muhammad Will Miss China Trip, Sports Illustrated Reports
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2012-08-15T04:01:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-15/ucla-s-muhammad-will-miss-china-trip-sports-illustrated-reports.html
Shabazz Muhammad won’t take part in
the University of California, Los Angeles’ three-game basketball
trip to China after he was declared ineligible, Sports
Illustrated reported, citing a source familiar with the plan.  The freshman is under investigation by the  National
Collegiate Athletic Association  for accepting improper benefits
from family friends, the magazine said.  Muhammad said he expected to be cleared in time for the
regular season, Sports Illustrated said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
 msillup@bloomberg.net  